Job Description:
Posting Title
Senior Package Designer

04/23/2020

Job Description
The Senior Package Designer is responsible for creating private brands and style guides for a variety of tool packaging. The Senior Package Designer will also will also assist in producing artwork for print using the latest Adobe Creative Cloud Suite of software for Macs, and work with various other departments to design projects that are brand supporting or supporting Harbor Freight marketing initiatives.
Essential Duties and Responsibilities:
Understand the value of the creative brief and the style guide, and be able to validate and support the guide in presenting work.
Develop, create and execute compelling high-impact designs for a variety of materials including product packaging and supporting brand and retail branding material.
Develop innovative and competitive product packaging art, establishing design direction and delivering design solutions, all with a solid understanding of brand architecture.
Create the style guides to support our initiatives in creating consistent brand ownership across a variety of package sizes and types.
Partner and assist leaders of the Harbor Freight Category Team in achieving their business objectives by analyzing information, strategizing solutions and translating all to strong visual concepts appropriate for the brand, audience, market, culture and business context.
Proven project management skills with the ability to work on multiple projects and organize workload to meet deadlines in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.
Assist and backup the Senior Manager with regard to proofing other designers work, reviewing designs in progress, represent department in regular staff meetings as needed by Senior Manager.
Demonstrate guidance to other designers who are not as familiar with the department processes, mentor designers if necessary.
Additional duties may be assigned.
Scope
Supervises staff - yes
Organization: working materials based on clear standards and naming conventions of Senior Manager of Brand and Packaging
Decision making-- Required with regard to brand to market strategy with key personnel in merchandising and global sourcing departments.
Travel--10%; may travel to trade show no more than once per year, domestic travel only.
